comments.text:
Because Rabbit took away all of his ammunition. How can somebody diss you 
with things that you just said about yourself? Also, he unloaded with a few 
things he heard about Papa Doc through the grapevine about his privileged 
upbringing. That is the reason he says, "Notice that this man did not have 
his hands up." Meaning: He ain't from here. Rabbit basically painted 
himself as the real down motherfucker who is local and struggling, and 
exposed Papa Doc as being the privileged outsider poser. Rabbit wasn't 
hiding his flaws, because he realized they were the things that set him 
apart from Papa Doc, and so basically, when it came to winning the crowd 
over, he was holding all the cards. Rabbit took all of his weaknesses and 
turned them into strengths, so much so that Papa Doc realized he had been 
destroyed and he forfeited.
